xdp-bench: Fix packet-operation values in documentation

Update the readme and manpage to match the values in xdp-bench.c.

Signed-off-by: Nimrod Oren <noren@nvidia.com>

xdp-bench: Add correct logging message for XDP_PASS

Before this commit, the XDP_TX message was used for the XDP_PASS case.

Signed-off-by: Nimrod Oren <noren@nvidia.com>

fix formula error in comment

Signed-off-by: ZENOTME <st810918843@gmail.com>

packaging/rpm: remove unneeded runtime dependency on kernel-header

Keep kernel-header dependency only in libxdp-devel, and not libxdp nor
libxdp-static, since those two does not strictly necessitate
compilation. Move the dependency to a BuildRequires instead.

Signed-off-by: Shung-Hsi Yu <shung-hsi.yu@suse.com>
[squash commits, move buildreq to top, adjust commit msg]
Signed-off-by: Toke Høiland-Jørgensen <toke@redhat.com>

make: remove *.ll when 'clean' has local override

Signed-off-by: Luca Boccassi <bluca@debian.org>

make: remove lib/testing/test-tool on clean

Signed-off-by: Luca Boccassi <bluca@debian.org>

Bump version to v1.4.2

Signed-off-by: Toke Høiland-Jørgensen <toke@redhat.com>

xdp-bench: Update man page

The man page was not rebuilt after the README file was updated to include the
l4-sport and l4-dport entries.

Signed-off-by: Toke Høiland-Jørgensen <toke@redhat.com>

Fix transposed calloc() arguments

Calls to calloc() are supposed to have the number of elements as the first
argument, but we erroneously transposed the arguments in a couple of places. It
seems GCC 14 has started to warn about this, which exposed this as build
breakage.

Signed-off-by: Toke Høiland-Jørgensen <toke@redhat.com>

Added support for clang-17 in configure script

Signed-off-by: Pavel Odintsov <pavel.odintsov@gmail.com>

libxdp: Fix xdp prog memory leak in xsk_setup_xdp_prog

In the xsk_setup_xdp_prog function, the xsk structure
temporarily takes ownership of an xdp_prog and stores it in
ctx->xdp_prog. However, the allocated memory is not freed
in xsk_destroy_xsk_struct, leading to a memory leak. This
commit addresses the issue by adding a call to
xdp_program_close to properly release the allocated
xdp_prog memory.

Signed-off-by: Ric Li <ming3.li@intel.com>

xdp-bench: Add l4-sport and l4-dport cpumap modes

These modes assigns CPUs based on L4 source and dest port. This is
useful for load testing scenarios where you can assign sequential source
ports to flows (like with neper).

For router/gateway use cases you use sport mapping on the forward
direction and dport mapping on the reverse direction.

Signed-off-by: Daniel Xu <dxu@dxuuu.xyz>

.github/workflows: Run mkarchive.sh directly from release workflow

We don't install all the prerequisites for building to the release workflow, and
because the 'make archive' target now inadvertently depends on config.mk, that
ends up trying to run configure, and then fail. Avoid this by just running the
mkarchive.sh script directly, now that it supports being run without a version
argument.

Signed-off-by: Toke Høiland-Jørgensen <toke@redhat.com>

mkarchive.sh: Default to current version

Add a conditionally defined target to version.mk that just prints the target,
and use that from mkarchive.sh to default to the current version if none is
supplied on the command line.

Signed-off-by: Toke Høiland-Jørgensen <toke@redhat.com>

Bump version to v1.4.1

Signed-off-by: Toke Høiland-Jørgensen <toke@redhat.com>

Rebuild man pages

Export now uses spaces for indentation.

Signed-off-by: Toke Høiland-Jørgensen <toke@redhat.com>

xdp-loader: Cast feature field when printing

Using the %llx format specifier leads to compiler warnings on some arches, use
%lx with an explicit cast to 'unsigned long' instead.

Signed-off-by: Toke Høiland-Jørgensen <toke@redhat.com>

configure: Don't fail on missing bpftool

Instead of bailing out of configure if bpftool is not found, just disable
compilation of the tools that require it (i.e., xdp-bench, xdp-monitor and
xdp-trafficgen which use BPF skeletons).

Signed-off-by: Toke Høiland-Jørgensen <toke@redhat.com>

libxdp: Move hard-coded -DLIBXDP_STATIC=1 compiler flag into a new
variable called STATIC_CFLAGS inline with the SHARED_CFLAGS variable
to improve Makefile consistency.

Signed-off-by: Alasdair McWilliam <alasdair.mcwilliam@outlook.com>

need to detach link for skb and native modes

Signed-off-by: Mohamed Mahmoud <mmahmoud@redhat.com>

Fix build on arm64

Fix the arm64 build by adding arch specific header files to
CFLAGS and BPF_CFLAGS. Also, use `gcc -print-multiarch` to get
arch name instead of `uname -m` which is not the right way.

Signed-off-by: Sachin Tiptur <coolsachints@gmail.com>

xdp-trafficgen: Cast argument to getsockname() to struct sockaddr

The must C library doesn't have the fancy union define that glibc has for
the various sockaddr structs, so it barfs on the use of a sockaddr_in6 as
an argument to getsockname(). Add an explicit cast to avoid the error.

Signed-off-by: Toke Høiland-Jørgensen <toke@redhat.com>

configure: Add check for presence of readelf

Since we're now using $READELF in the libxdp Makefile, we should make sure the
utility is present (and the variable set), or we may get weird 'make' errors.

Signed-off-by: Toke Høiland-Jørgensen <toke@redhat.com>

Support detaching bpf_link-based attachments

When explicitly detaching from an interface we should also handle bpf_link-based
attachments (by force-detaching the link).

Fixes #361.

Signed-off-by: Mohamed Mahmoud <mmahmoud@redhat.com>

packaging/rpm: Change License field to be SPDX-compliant

Fedora has a policy that the License field of all packages should be in SPDX
format, so update the values in the .spec file in this repo. Also add separate
license fields for the libxdp subpackages since they are licensed differently
than the main xdp-tools package.

Signed-off-by: Toke Høiland-Jørgensen <toke@redhat.com>

xdp-bench: flushing output buffers after printing stats

Having buffering enabled (by default in linux) for `stdout`
causes issues for pipes. Since pipe buffer is pretty large
(64KiB) it would take ages to fill that up. Therefore,
applications in pipe are "unable" to reliably read
`xdp-bench`'s `stdout`.

This approach may affect performance but since `xdp-bench` tool
does not rely on `stdout`/`stderr` operations, it's safe to flush both
`stdout` and `stderr` buffers immediately.

Signed-off-by: Samuel Dobron <sdobron@redhat.com>

libxdp: Fix bpf program original file  descriptor management

Signed-off-by: Marcin Knap <m.knap@falconvsystems.com>

New versions of bpftool fail to compile on clang-11, so let's just bump the
